ce:section.ce:para:
STEM images of SnS and SnS2 powders are presented in Figs. 5 and 6

                     , together with the area from which EDX spectra were collected. EDX measurements confirm the elemental composition and stoichiometry of obtained powders (see Table 1
                     ). SnS occurred in the form of large agglomerates (diameter c. a. 1 μm) of smaller particles (as revealed by STEM images). SnS2 showed interesting flower-like morphology. Previously, Khimani et al. sonochemically have synthesized nanoparticles of SnS2 with spherical morphology [14].
